  <text>
      <body>
         <p>Isis to RC. As a weary traveller pants, and thirsteth, after water so my heart longs for your letters: i wrote this much just when the Isis came in so, was obliged to give it up. i intended writing you a few lines, but must now content myself and you, by referring you to the 63 Psalm, particularly the 6 verse "I remember three upon my bed, and meditate on thee in the night." Let me beg you to keep the letter sent to day, and return yours to me I can make a very good use of it, do love has [sic] i request you, [.] I have scarcely looked at an Isis, but shall do so this evening. In the Psalm mentioned read, R.C. for God!
            [[2]] The Isis are really sailed[?] this evening; Mr Cousins says they have had to work in the night. which is excusable.</p>
